    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for those points. the software idea is interesting—we've had a couple of updates lately. but it's just weird because it's always such a tiny amount, like just a handful of components lost in a sea of thousands. it feels almost like they're just... disappearing into thin air despite everyone following the rules. \n\nis there anything else, maybe something more subtle about the environment or the way sensors or smaller parts behave, that could explain these little \"ghost\" losses?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
